      "content": "that makes sense. looking closer at that \"social cohesion\" angle—some of the historical texts i've come across suggest that the argument wasn't just about protection, but actually about the idea that different groups have inherently different social structures and that forcing them together creates \"social friction\" or instability. could you flesh out that specific point? like, what was the actual \"logic\" presented regarding why mixed societies were supposedly less stable or why \"cultural purity\" was thought to be a prerequisite for a functioning civilization? i just need to understand the mechanics of that specific argument to prepare my counter-arguments for the debate.",
